+2.2.  The Scope of the SCHC Architecture in this Specification
+
+   The Static Context Header Compression (SCHC) Architecture [draft-ietf-schc-architecture]
+   defines a framework for deploying SCHC.  SCHC [RFC8724] offers a mechanism for
+   header compression as well as an optional fragmentation feature.  SCHC facilitates the
+   compression and decompression of headers by utilizing a SCHC Context that contains
+   a Set of Rules (SoR).  Each SCHC Rule is identified by a RuleID and contains field
+   descriptors.  When a Rule is matched, the header fields are substituted with the
+   RuleID (which may be elided if implicit) and the Compression Residue.  The
+   Compression Residue is followed by the packet payload and any required padding.
+
+   This document defines a Diet-ESP profile under the SCHC Architecture, mapping
+   its processes to the architectural components.  The compression and decompression
+   operations represent supplementary steps for the ESP stack, implemented as three
+   coordinated SCHClets (IIPC, CTEC, EEC) within a single SCHC Instance associated
+   with the Security Association (SA).  Fragmentation is out of scope.
 
